&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pharmacist Technician – Prison Services, Band 4/5&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Prison and Forensic Directorate&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;x4 Full time, 37.5 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Oxleas NHS Foundation Trust is a mental health and community trust that provides a wide and growing range of services across the boroughs of Bexley, Greenwich and Bromley. The Forensic and Prison Directorate hold contracts for prisons within Kent and South East London and as part of these contract provides pharmacy services to these prisons.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Oxleas Prison Services Ltd (OPS) is a wholly owned subsidiary of Oxleas NHS Trust set up to provide the pharmacy prison services. Posts recruited to for prison pharmacy are employed by Oxleas NHS Trust and seconded to OPS. Our pharmacy services are innovative and drive medicines optimization within our prisons.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We believe in supporting our staff to develop to their full potential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are currently seeking:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;x4 Pharmacy Technicians – Prison Services Band 4/5&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are a pharmacy technician wishing to gain experience in working in a prison setting, this post could be for you. The post-holders will provide pharmacy technical services, including medicines management and administration services to a cluster of prisons. You will also work in the busy dispensaries. You will be supported and mentored by the Senior Prison Services Technician. You will be an integral part of the pharmacy team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post-holders will be based at the Greenwich Cluster of prisons (HMP Belmarsh/HMP Thameside) and will rotate between prisons.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hai Nguyen&lt;br /&gt;Lead Prisons Services Pharmacist &lt;br /&gt;hai.nguyen1@nhs.net 0207 1475022 (Belmarsh)&lt;/p&gt;
